"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-23-2024-olympic-qualifier-waldrum-names-oshoala-nnadozie-ajibade-starting-line-up-vs-cameroon\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons head coach, Randy Waldrum has released his starting line-up for tonight's Olympic Games qualifying fixture against the Indomitable Lionesses of Cameroon.  Paris FC's Chiamaka Nnadozie will start in goal.  Michelle Alozie, Osinachi Ohale, Oluwatosin Demehin and Ashleigh Plumptre will operate from the defence.  The midfield trio comprises of Halimat Ayinde, Christy Ucheibe and Deborah Abiodun.  Africa's women's best player, Asisat Oshoala will lead the attack.  Oshoala will be supported by Rasheedat Ajibade and Toni Payne.  The encounter billed for Stade de la Reunification, Douala will kick-off at 6pm.  Super Falcons X1 Vs Cameroon  Nnadozie  Alozie, Ohale, Demehin, Plumptre  Ayinde, Ucheibe, Abiodun  Ajibade, Oshoala, Payne.  Bayelsa United's Ogundare set to return against Akwa United  Carabao Cup final: Chelsea get double boost ahead of Liverpool clash  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons ready to defend title - Nnadozie  WAFCON 2026: Madugu drops Oshoala, lists 25 players for Cameroon friendlies  UCL play-off: Oshoala predicts Benfica vs Real Madrid clash  NWFL: Delta Queens appoint Ajibade new head coach  Nnadozie scoops English Women's League Save of the Month award  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"